------------------------------------------------------------------------------
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
KotakeeOS - Home Management System
Speech Recognition Application Server
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Description:

Root programs for speech recognition application server designed to interface 
with the kotakeeOS Web Server. This sends requests to activate-deactivate 
modules just like any other regular web application. 

Currently utilizes python speechrecognition library for command parsing, with
the following options for passive hotword detection:

- PocketSphinx (brute force, essentially)
- Trigger Word Models
  - Iteration 0, the pretrained model on "activate"
  - Iterations > 0, models trained experimentally on the same/other hotwords. 

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Prerequisites
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

1. Python3
2. python3 -m pip install speechrecognition
3. python3 -m pip install pyttsx3
4. brew install portaudio
5. python3 -m pip install pyaudio

If using PocketSphinx: 

6. brew install swig
7. brew install openal-soft
8. Note the stuff you may need to do to install pockeshpinx manually.

https://github.com/bambocher/pocketsphinx-python/issues/28

If using homebrewed Trigger Word models:

6. cd ../triggerWordDetection
7. pip3 install -r requirements.txt
8. You may need to install more requirements beyond these. 

Once you've installed those, the TriggerWord speech server should work
just fine. 
